triples.evidence: We want R1 to be large so that most of the input voltage appears across it, ensuring we capture as much of the signal as possible.

evidence: In the example at the bottom right, R S is our sensor, whose resistance changes slightly by a factor of x in response to something like temperature or pressure. R_L is the load resistor. If x equals zero, the sensor is at its nominal value. When x changes, even by a small amount, the output voltage V out changes.
